An insurer may retain any of the following persons to take charge of damage assessment: <Amended by Act No. 12945, Dec. 30, 2014; Act No. 14839, Jul. 26, 2017>
* person prescribed by Ordinance of the Ministry of the Interior and Safety among certified damage adjusters under ;
* damage evaluator.
* minor;
* person under adult guardianship or a person under limited guardianship;
* person for whom two years have not elapsed since his/her imprisonment without labor
